tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE UserActivityData (
  user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  activity_type VARCHAR,
  activity_duration INT,
  activity_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50),
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    height FLOAT,
    weight FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE user_activity (
    activity_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    activity_type VARCHAR(50),
    duration INT,
    calories_burned FLOAT,
    activity_date DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id)
);

CREATE TABLE user_activity_data (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  activity_type VARCHAR(255),
  duration_minutes INT,
  date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE workout_plans (
  plan_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  plan_name VARCHAR(255),
  intensity_level VARCHAR(50),
  duration_days INT
)

CREATE TABLE user_workouts (
  workout_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  plan_id INT,
  workout_date DATE,
  completed BOOLEAN
)

CREATE TABLE UserActivity (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    activity_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    activity_duration INT NOT NULL,
    activity_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE WorkoutPlan (
    plan_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    plan_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    plan_description TEXT,
    plan_duration INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES UserActivity(user_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Exercise (
    exercise_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    exercise_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    exercise_category VARCHAR(50),
    calories_burned_per_hour FLOAT,
    equipment_needed BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE UserPreferences (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    height FLOAT,
    weight FLOAT,
    age INT,
    fitness_level VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE user_workouts (
    user_id INT,
    workout_id INT,
    date_completed DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (workout_id) REFERENCES workouts(workout_id)
);

CREATE TABLE workout_exercises (
    workout_id INT,
    exercise_id INT,
    sets INT,
    reps INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (workout_id) REFERENCES workouts(workout_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (exercise_id) REFERENCES exercises(exercise_id)
);
